    message: >
      Created integrations/opencode-plugin/codedna.js — OpenCode JS plugin using
      tool.execute.after and event (session.idle) hooks. Supports 11 languages:
      Python, TS, JS, Go, PHP, Rust, Java, Kotlin, Ruby, C#, Swift.
      Detection mirrors base.py has_codedna_header(): scan first 30 lines,
      strip comment prefix (//, #, """), check for exports:/used_by:.
      For write tool: checks full content. For edit tool: checks new_string patch
      only if it introduces a new top-level definition (heuristic via regex).
      install.sh now installs both AGENTS.md and codedna.js when target is opencode.
      Open: tool.execute.after hook signature (input vs output for args) is inferred
       from docs — needs verification against live OpenCode instance.

